      "rawMarkdown": "## 2. Amorphous\n\n**Pronunciation:** ə-MOR-fəs\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Having no clear shape, form, or structure.\n**Bangla meaning:** নির্দিষ্ট আকারহীন, অস্পষ্ট গঠনের\n**Root story:** Greek *a-* = without + *morphē* = form. So, **amorphous = without form**.\n**Simple explanation:** Something amorphous has no fixed shape or clear organization.\n**Memory hook:** **A + morph = no form.**\n**GRE synonyms:** nebulous, vague, indeterminate, formless, shapeless\n**Basic synonyms:** unclear, loose, undefined, unstructured\n**Antonyms:** structured, definite, clear, organized, well-formed\n**Common usage:** amorphous idea, amorphous mass, amorphous plan, amorphous concept\n**Confusing word:** **Amorphous ≠ Ambiguous**. Amorphous = shape/structure unclear; ambiguous = meaning unclear.\n**Final memory:** **Amorphous = without clear form = আকারহীন / অস্পষ্ট**\n\n### 10 Examples\n\n1. The cloud looked amorphous.\n2. The jelly became an amorphous mass.\n3. His drawing was amorphous and hard to identify.\n4. The proposal was criticized for being amorphous.\n5. His argument remained amorphous and difficult to evaluate.\n6. The committee rejected the amorphous plan.\n7. The company had an amorphous management structure.\n8. In materials science, amorphous solids lack a regular crystal structure.\n9. In policy writing, an amorphous goal is hard to measure.\n10. The theory sounded impressive but remained too amorphous to test.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15 Sentences\n\n1. The politician gave a **nebulous** answer to avoid responsibility.\n2. Her career goals were still **nebulous** after graduation.\n3. The contract contained **nebulous** terms that confused both parties.\n4. The committee disliked the **nebulous** proposal.\n5. The concept of fairness can become **nebulous** in complex legal cases.\n6. His explanation was too **vague** to be useful.\n7. The witness gave a **vague** description of the thief.\n8. The research question remained **vague** and unfocused.\n9. The instructions were **vague**, so the students made different mistakes.\n10. The manager’s **vague** promises failed to reassure employees.\n11. The result was **indeterminate** because the data were incomplete.\n12. The experiment produced an **indeterminate** outcome.\n13. His answer was **indeterminate**, neither yes nor no.\n14. The disease had **indeterminate** symptoms at first.\n15. The legal status of the document remained **indeterminate**.\n\n---",
