      "rawMarkdown": "## 3. Austere\n\n**Pronunciation:** aw-STEER\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Strict, plain, severe, without luxury.\n**Bangla meaning:** কঠোর, সাদাসিধে, আড়ম্বরহীন\n**Root story:** From Greek/Latin ideas of “harsh, dry, bitter.” Later it came to mean strict or plain.\n**Simple explanation:** Austere means simple and strict, often with little comfort or decoration.\n**Memory hook:** **Austere monk = simple life, no luxury.**\n**GRE synonyms:** severe, stern, ascetic, Spartan, rigid\n**Basic synonyms:** strict, plain, simple, harsh\n**Antonyms:** luxurious, indulgent, ornate, soft, lavish\n**Common usage:** austere lifestyle, austere room, austere policy, austere discipline\n**Confusing word:** **Austere ≠ Aesthetic**. Austere = strict/plain; aesthetic = related to beauty.\n**Final memory:** **Austere = strict + plain = কঠোর ও সাদাসিধে**\n\n### 10 Examples\n\n1. The monk lived an austere life.\n2. The room was austere and undecorated.\n3. His father was austere but fair.\n4. The government introduced austere economic measures.\n5. The professor’s austere manner frightened new students.\n6. The building’s austere design avoided unnecessary decoration.\n7. During the crisis, the family adopted an austere budget.\n8. In architecture, austere design often emphasizes function over ornament.\n9. In economic reports, austerity programs often involve austere spending limits.\n10. The leader’s austere public image helped him appear disciplined.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15 Sentences\n\n1. The judge gave the criminal a **severe** sentence.\n2. The region suffered **severe** food shortages.\n3. The professor’s criticism was **severe** but accurate.\n4. The company faced **severe** financial pressure.\n5. The new policy imposed **severe** restrictions on spending.\n6. Her **stern** warning silenced the class.\n7. The principal had a **stern** expression.\n8. The report offered a **stern** assessment of the project’s failures.\n9. His **stern** discipline helped the team improve.\n10. The government took a **stern** position against corruption.\n11. The monk followed an **ascetic** lifestyle.\n12. His **ascetic** habits surprised his wealthy friends.\n13. The room’s **Spartan** design had only a bed and a desk.\n14. The soldiers lived in **Spartan** conditions.\n15. The school’s **rigid** rules left little room for creativity.\n\n---",
