      "rawMarkdown": "## 13. Disseminate\n\n**Pronunciation:** dih-SEM-ə-nayt\n**Part of speech:** Verb\n**Core meaning:** To spread information, ideas, or knowledge widely.\n**Bangla meaning:** ছড়িয়ে দেওয়া, প্রচার করা, বিস্তার করা\n**Root story:** Latin *dis-* = in different directions + *semen* = seed. Disseminate = scatter seeds.\n**Simple explanation:** To disseminate means to spread something so many people receive it.\n**Memory hook:** **Disseminate = scatter seeds of information.**\n**GRE synonyms:** circulate, propagate, distribute, broadcast, spread\n**Basic synonyms:** share, publish, send out, make known\n**Antonyms:** suppress, conceal, withhold, hide\n**Common usage:** disseminate information, disseminate findings, disseminate propaganda\n**Confusing word:** **Disseminate ≠ Discriminate**. Disseminate = spread; discriminate = differentiate or treat unfairly.\n**Final memory:** **Disseminate = spread like seeds = ছড়িয়ে দেওয়া**\n\n### 10 Examples\n\n1. The school disseminated the notice.\n2. Please disseminate this information.\n3. The news disseminated quickly.\n4. Researchers disseminated their findings through a journal.\n5. Governments disseminate health warnings during outbreaks.\n6. The organization disseminated educational materials.\n7. False information can disseminate rapidly online.\n8. Conferences disseminate new research ideas.\n9. Agencies disseminate emergency instructions through radio and mobile alerts.\n10. Weak communication can prevent life-saving information from being disseminated.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15 Sentences\n\n1. The memo was **circulated** among all employees.\n2. The rumor **circulated** quickly through the campus.\n3. The journal **circulated** the new findings to researchers.\n4. False claims **circulated** online after the accident.\n5. The committee **circulated** the draft before voting.\n6. The organization tried to **propagate** scientific knowledge.\n7. Extremist groups may **propagate** dangerous ideas.\n8. The campaign **propagated** awareness about clean water.\n9. Schools can **propagate** values of tolerance and honesty.\n10. Social media can **propagate** both truth and misinformation.\n11. The charity **distributed** food after the flood.\n12. The agency **distributed** safety guidelines to factories.\n13. The government **broadcast** emergency warnings.\n14. Scientists **published** their findings in a respected journal.\n15. The group **spread** awareness about renewable energy.\n\n---",
