      "rawMarkdown": "## 15. Flout\n\n**Pronunciation:** FLOWT\n**Part of speech:** Verb\n**Core meaning:** To openly disobey or show contempt for a rule, law, or custom.\n**Bangla meaning:** প্রকাশ্যে অমান্য করা, অবজ্ঞা করা\n**Root story:** Origin uncertain; the uploaded note connects it with “mock/jeer/scoff” senses. \n**Simple explanation:** To flout a rule means to break it openly and disrespectfully.\n**Memory hook:** **Flout law = laugh at law.**\n**GRE synonyms:** defy, disregard, scorn, violate, contravene\n**Basic synonyms:** disobey, ignore, break, reject\n**Antonyms:** obey, respect, follow, comply with\n**Common usage:** flout the law, flout rules, flout convention, flout authority\n**Confusing word:** **Flout ≠ Flaunt**. Flout = disobey; flaunt = show off.\n**Final memory:** **Flout = openly disobey = প্রকাশ্যে অমান্য করা**\n\n### 10 Examples\n\n1. He flouted the rule.\n2. The driver flouted the traffic law.\n3. Students should not flout school rules.\n4. The company flouted environmental regulations.\n5. The politician flouted democratic norms.\n6. The rebels flouted the curfew.\n7. The institution was punished for flouting safety standards.\n8. Factories that flout safety rules expose workers to serious risk.\n9. Firms may flout pollution limits to reduce costs.\n10. States that flout treaties damage international trust.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15 Sentences\n\n1. The activist chose to **defy** the unjust order.\n2. The company **defied** safety regulations and was fined.\n3. The rebel group **defied** the government’s warning.\n4. His actions **defied** social expectations.\n5. The student **defied** the teacher’s instruction.\n6. The manager **disregarded** repeated warnings.\n7. The factory **disregarded** environmental rules.\n8. He **disregarded** expert advice and failed.\n9. The policy **disregarded** the needs of rural workers.\n10. The driver **disregarded** the traffic signal.\n11. The dictator **scorned** democratic principles.\n12. The official **violated** public trust.\n13. The company **violated** the contract.\n14. The action **contravened** international law.\n15. The group **ignored** the court’s order.\n\n---\n\n# Compact Daily Summary Table — Day 1 Part 1\n\n| No. | Word        | Core Meaning               | Bangla               | GRE Synonyms                         | Antonym      |\n| --: | ----------- | -------------------------- | -------------------- | ------------------------------------ | ------------ |\n|   1 | Abound      | exist in large quantity    | প্রচুর থাকা          | teem, proliferate, swarm             | lack         |\n|   2 | Amorphous   | without clear shape        | আকারহীন              | nebulous, vague, indeterminate       | structured   |\n|   3 | Austere     | strict, plain, severe      | কঠোর, সাদাসিধে       | severe, stern, ascetic               | luxurious    |\n|   4 | Belie       | give false impression      | মিথ্যা ধারণা দেওয়া   | contradict, negate, disprove         | reveal       |\n|   5 | Capricious  | unpredictable              | খামখেয়ালী            | fickle, whimsical, mercurial         | stable       |\n|   6 | Cerebral    | intellectual/brain-related | বুদ্ধিবৃত্তিক        | intellectual, analytical, rational   | emotional    |\n|   7 | Congenial   | pleasant/suitable          | অনুকূল               | agreeable, compatible, pleasant      | hostile      |\n|   8 | Conspicuous | easy to notice             | লক্ষণীয়              | prominent, noticeable, obvious       | hidden       |\n|   9 | Cursory     | quick and shallow          | উপর উপর              | superficial, hasty, perfunctory      | thorough     |\n|  10 | Daunting    | difficult/frightening      | ভীতিকর কঠিন          | intimidating, formidable, forbidding | easy         |\n|  11 | Deify       | glorify like a god         | দেবতা বানানো         | venerate, glorify, exalt             | criticize    |\n|  12 | Didactic    | intended to teach          | শিক্ষামূলক           | instructive, pedagogical, preachy    | entertaining |\n|  13 | Disseminate | spread widely              | ছড়িয়ে দেওয়া          | circulate, propagate, distribute     | suppress     |\n|  14 | Feasible    | practical to do            | বাস্তবায়নযোগ্য       | practicable, viable, achievable      | impossible   |\n|  15 | Flout       | openly disobey             | প্রকাশ্যে অমান্য করা | defy, disregard, scorn               | obey         |\n\n---\n\n# Revision Section\n\nStudy this set in 4 rounds:\n\n**Round 1 — Meaning:** Read the core meaning + Bangla meaning.\n**Round 2 — Memory:** Say the memory hook aloud.\n**Round 3 — GRE Synonyms:** For each word, recall 2 GRE synonyms.\n**Round 4 — Usage:** Make one sentence from memory.\n\nHigh-priority GRE words from this set: **belie, capricious, cursory, daunting, flout, disseminate, feasible, conspicuous**.\n\n---\n\n# Day 1 GRE Vocabulary — Part 2\n\n## Words 16–30\n\nSource word list confirmed from your uploaded/previous Day vocabulary file: **Homogeneous, Humdrum, Insipid, Loquacious, Misanthropic, Misnomer, Negligent, Obsequious, Placate, Proclivity, Puerile, Quixotic, Spendthrift, Taciturn, Wary**. \n\n---",
