      "rawMarkdown": "## 21. Misnomer\n\n**Pronunciation:** mis-NOH-mər\n**Part of speech:** Noun\n**Core meaning:** A wrong or inaccurate name.\n**Bangla meaning:** ভুল নাম, ভুল উপাধি, ভুল শব্দপ্রয়োগ\n**Root story:** **mis-** = wrong + root related to **name**. So **misnomer = wrong name**.\n**Simple explanation:** A misnomer is a label that does not correctly describe the thing.\n**Memory hook:** **Mis + name = misnomer.**\n**GRE synonyms:** misnaming, inaccurate label, wrong designation, mislabeling, inaccuracy\n**Basic synonyms:** wrong name, wrong term, false label\n**Antonyms:** accurate name, correct label, proper term\n**Common usage:** common misnomer, scientific misnomer, historical misnomer, legal misnomer\n**Confusing word:** **Misnomer ≠ Mispronunciation**. Misnomer = wrong name; mispronunciation = wrong sound.\n**Final memory:** **Misnomer = wrong name = ভুল নাম**\n\n### 10 Examples\n\n1. Calling a koala a bear is a misnomer.\n2. “Starfish” is a misnomer because it is not a fish.\n3. The nickname was a misnomer.\n4. The term “Dark Ages” may be considered a historical misnomer.\n5. Calling the policy “reform” was a misnomer because it changed little.\n6. “Free market” can be a misnomer when heavy regulation exists.\n7. The committee argued that “temporary tax” was a misnomer.\n8. Common animal names can be misnomers because they ignore scientific classification.\n9. “Artificial intelligence” can be a misnomer for simple automation.\n10. “Affordable housing” is a misnomer if prices remain beyond workers’ income.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15 Sentences\n\n1. The term is an **inaccurate label** for the new policy.\n2. Calling the office “independent” was an **inaccurate label** because it answered to the minister.\n3. The phrase “clean coal” may be considered an **inaccurate label** by critics.\n4. The species received a **wrong designation** in early reports.\n5. The document used a **wrong designation** for the legal category.\n6. The researcher corrected the **misnaming** of the compound.\n7. The **misnaming** confused students during the biology lesson.\n8. The product’s title involved **mislabeling**.\n9. The court punished the company for **mislabeling** medical devices.\n10. The report contained an **inaccuracy** in its classification.\n11. The label was **misleading** because the product was not organic.\n12. The phrase created a **false label** for a complex issue.\n13. The outdated term was a **poor name** for the disease.\n14. The category was a **misclassification**.\n15. The name was **imprecise**, though popular.\n\n---",
