      "rawMarkdown": "## 25. Proclivity\n\n**Pronunciation:** proh-KLIV-ə-tee\n**Part of speech:** Noun\n**Core meaning:** A natural tendency or inclination toward something.\n**Bangla meaning:** প্রবণতা, ঝোঁক, স্বাভাবিক আগ্রহ\n**Root story:** Latin **pro-** = forward + **clivus** = slope. A proclivity is like a natural slope that pulls you toward something.\n**Simple explanation:** If you have a proclivity for something, you tend to do it or like it naturally.\n**Memory hook:** **Proclivity = your mind slopes toward it.**\n**GRE synonyms:** inclination, propensity, predisposition, tendency, penchant\n**Basic synonyms:** habit, leaning, preference, tendency\n**Antonyms:** aversion, dislike, disinclination, repulsion\n**Common usage:** proclivity for risk, proclivity toward violence, proclivity for analysis, artistic proclivity\n**Confusing word:** **Proclivity ≠ Productivity**. Proclivity = tendency; productivity = output/efficiency.\n**Final memory:** **Proclivity = natural tendency = প্রবণতা**\n\n### 10 Examples\n\n1. He has a proclivity for music.\n2. She has a proclivity for solving puzzles.\n3. The child showed a proclivity for drawing.\n4. Investors with a proclivity for risk may prefer volatile markets.\n5. His proclivity for exaggeration made people doubt his stories.\n6. The manager’s proclivity for micromanagement frustrated employees.\n7. The study examined genetic proclivity toward certain diseases.\n8. Some students have a proclivity for analytical thinking.\n9. A leader’s proclivity for secrecy can damage public trust.\n10. The author’s proclivity for irony shapes the tone of the novel.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15 Sentences\n\n1. She has an **inclination** toward mathematics.\n2. His **inclination** to avoid conflict made him a careful negotiator.\n3. The committee showed an **inclination** to support reform.\n4. Her **inclination** for research appeared early.\n5. The patient had a **propensity** for allergic reactions.\n6. Some investors have a **propensity** to panic during downturns.\n7. His **propensity** for risk made him unsuitable for the role.\n8. The data suggest a **propensity** toward relapse.\n9. The child had a **predisposition** to asthma.\n10. Family history may indicate a **predisposition** to diabetes.\n11. The leader had a **tendency** to centralize power.\n12. His **tendency** to interrupt annoyed colleagues.\n13. She has a **penchant** for complex novels.\n14. The director has a **penchant** for dark humor.\n15. His natural **leaning** toward caution helped the team avoid mistakes.\n\n---",
