      "rawMarkdown": "## 27. Quixotic\n\n**Pronunciation:** kwik-SOT-ik\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Extremely idealistic but unrealistic.\n**Bangla meaning:** অবাস্তব আদর্শবাদী, কল্পনাপ্রসূত, বাস্তবতাহীন\n**Root story:** From **Don Quixote**, a literary character who pursued noble but unrealistic adventures.\n**Simple explanation:** A quixotic plan may sound noble, beautiful, or heroic, but it is not practical.\n**Memory hook:** **Quixotic = Don Quixote fighting windmills.**\n**GRE synonyms:** idealistic, impractical, visionary, unrealistic, romantic\n**Basic synonyms:** dreamy, unrealistic, impossible, overly idealistic\n**Antonyms:** practical, realistic, pragmatic, sensible\n**Common usage:** quixotic plan, quixotic dream, quixotic campaign, quixotic reform\n**Confusing word:** **Quixotic ≠ Exotic**. Quixotic = unrealistic idealism; exotic = foreign/unusual.\n**Final memory:** **Quixotic = noble but unrealistic = অবাস্তব আদর্শবাদী**\n\n### 10 Examples\n\n1. His plan was quixotic.\n2. Ending all crime in one week is quixotic.\n3. Her dream was noble but quixotic.\n4. The reformer’s quixotic campaign inspired people but failed politically.\n5. The proposal was dismissed as quixotic because it ignored cost.\n6. The entrepreneur’s quixotic vision attracted attention but not funding.\n7. A quixotic war against all corruption cannot succeed without institutions.\n8. Some climate plans sound quixotic unless supported by technology and policy.\n9. The project’s quixotic ambition exceeded available resources.\n10. The senator’s quixotic promise appealed to idealists but worried economists.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15 Sentences\n\n1. The proposal was **idealistic** but poorly planned.\n2. Her **idealistic** view of politics ignored human self-interest.\n3. The movement began with **idealistic** hopes.\n4. An **idealistic** leader may inspire people but overlook practical limits.\n5. The plan was **impractical** because it required impossible funding.\n6. The design looked elegant but was **impractical** for mass production.\n7. The policy was morally attractive but **impractical**.\n8. His **visionary** proposal imagined a new kind of city.\n9. The inventor was **visionary**, though not always realistic.\n10. The project had a **visionary** goal but no workable method.\n11. The schedule was **unrealistic**.\n12. The budget assumptions were **unrealistic**.\n13. The campaign made **romantic** promises about rural life.\n14. The dream was **utopian**, not practical.\n15. The plan was **overambitious** for a small team.\n\n---",
