      "rawMarkdown": "## 28. Spendthrift\n\n**Pronunciation:** SPEND-thrift\n**Part of speech:** Noun / Adjective\n**Core meaning:** A person who spends money recklessly; wasteful with money.\n**Bangla meaning:** অমিতব্যয়ী, অপব্যয়ী, টাকা উড়ায় এমন\n**Root story:** **Spend** + **thrift**. Ironically, a spendthrift has no thrift; he spends instead of saving.\n**Simple explanation:** A spendthrift wastes money without careful planning.\n**Memory hook:** **Spend + thrift = spends away thrift.**\n**GRE synonyms:** profligate, extravagant, wasteful, prodigal, improvident\n**Basic synonyms:** reckless spender, money-waster, overspender\n**Antonyms:** frugal, thrifty, economical, prudent\n**Common usage:** spendthrift heir, spendthrift habits, spendthrift lifestyle, spendthrift government\n**Confusing word:** **Spendthrift ≠ Thrifty**. Spendthrift = wasteful; thrifty = careful with money.\n**Final memory:** **Spendthrift = reckless spender = অমিতব্যয়ী**\n\n### 10 Examples\n\n1. He is a spendthrift.\n2. The spendthrift son wasted his inheritance.\n3. Her spendthrift habits worried her parents.\n4. The company collapsed under spendthrift management.\n5. The king’s spendthrift lifestyle emptied the treasury.\n6. A spendthrift government may create long-term debt.\n7. The novel criticizes a spendthrift aristocracy.\n8. Spendthrift policies can become dangerous during economic downturns.\n9. A spendthrift consumer may confuse luxury with necessity.\n10. The heir’s spendthrift behavior contrasted with his father’s frugality.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15 Sentences\n\n1. The **profligate** ruler wasted public money on palaces.\n2. His **profligate** spending destroyed the family business.\n3. The report criticized the department’s **profligate** use of funds.\n4. The empire weakened under **profligate** leadership.\n5. Her **extravagant** lifestyle exceeded her income.\n6. The wedding was beautiful but **extravagant**.\n7. The company rejected **extravagant** office renovations.\n8. The minister defended the **extravagant** project.\n9. The project was **wasteful**, consuming resources without benefit.\n10. **Wasteful** habits can ruin a budget.\n11. The **prodigal** son returned after wasting his inheritance.\n12. The CEO’s **prodigal** spending alarmed investors.\n13. His **improvident** choices left him with no savings.\n14. The family suffered because of **improvident** financial planning.\n15. The council condemned the **reckless** expenditure.\n\n---",
