      "rawMarkdown": "## 29. Taciturn\n\n**Pronunciation:** TAS-i-turn\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Habitually quiet; not talkative.\n**Bangla meaning:** স্বল্পভাষী, কম কথা বলে এমন, চুপচাপ\n**Root story:** Latin **tacere** = to be silent. So **taciturn = silent by habit**.\n**Simple explanation:** A taciturn person usually speaks very little.\n**Memory hook:** **Taciturn = turns tacit/silent.**\n**GRE synonyms:** reserved, reticent, silent, uncommunicative, laconic\n**Basic synonyms:** quiet, shy, brief, not talkative\n**Antonyms:** loquacious, talkative, garrulous, voluble\n**Common usage:** taciturn man, taciturn leader, taciturn colleague, taciturn response\n**Confusing word:** **Taciturn ≠ Tacit**. Taciturn = quiet person; tacit = understood without being said.\n**Final memory:** **Taciturn = habitually quiet = স্বল্পভাষী**\n\n### 10 Examples\n\n1. He is taciturn in class.\n2. The taciturn guard answered with one word.\n3. My grandfather was kind but taciturn.\n4. The taciturn witness gave only brief answers.\n5. The CEO’s taciturn style made reporters impatient.\n6. His taciturn nature was mistaken for arrogance.\n7. The novel’s hero is taciturn but deeply thoughtful.\n8. A taciturn leader may appear calm during crisis.\n9. In interviews, taciturn candidates may seem less confident.\n10. His taciturn response contrasted with his colleague’s long explanation.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15 Sentences\n\n1. The **reserved** student rarely spoke in class.\n2. His **reserved** manner made him difficult to read.\n3. The ambassador remained **reserved** during negotiations.\n4. She was friendly but **reserved** with strangers.\n5. The witness was **reticent** about the details.\n6. The company was **reticent** to reveal financial data.\n7. He became **reticent** after the controversy.\n8. The patient was **reticent** during the interview.\n9. The monk remained **silent** throughout the meal.\n10. The committee was **silent** on the most serious accusation.\n11. His **uncommunicative** style frustrated colleagues.\n12. The suspect was **uncommunicative** during questioning.\n13. The soldier gave a **laconic** reply: “No.”\n14. Her **laconic** email contained only three words.\n15. His **brief** answer suggested discomfort.\n\n---",
