      "rawMarkdown": "## 30. Wary\n\n**Pronunciation:** WAIR-ee\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Careful because there may be danger, risk, or deception.\n**Bangla meaning:** সতর্ক, সাবধান, সজাগ\n**Root story:** Related to the idea of being aware and watchful.\n**Simple explanation:** If you are wary, you do not trust immediately; you stay cautious.\n**Memory hook:** **Wary = aware of danger.**\n**GRE synonyms:** cautious, vigilant, watchful, circumspect, guarded\n**Basic synonyms:** careful, alert, suspicious, careful-minded\n**Antonyms:** reckless, careless, naive, unwary\n**Common usage:** wary investor, wary of strangers, wary of risks, wary response\n**Confusing word:** **Wary ≠ Weary**. Wary = cautious; weary = tired.\n**Final memory:** **Wary = cautious about danger = সতর্ক**\n\n### 10 Examples\n\n1. Be wary of strangers.\n2. Investors are wary of sudden market changes.\n3. She was wary of online scams.\n4. The doctor was wary of treatments with weak evidence.\n5. The engineer remained wary of small cracks in the structure.\n6. Consumers became wary after the company’s false claims.\n7. The committee was wary of approving a costly project.\n8. Users should be wary of suspicious links.\n9. Researchers are wary of drawing conclusions from limited data.\n10. Safety teams remain wary of small defects that may grow under stress.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15 Sentences\n\n1. The investor remained **cautious** during the market crash.\n2. A **cautious** researcher avoids exaggerated conclusions.\n3. The driver was **cautious** on the wet road.\n4. The committee took a **cautious** approach to reform.\n5. The guard stayed **vigilant** throughout the night.\n6. Citizens must remain **vigilant** against misinformation.\n7. The doctor was **vigilant** for signs of infection.\n8. The security team stayed **watchful** near the entrance.\n9. Parents were **watchful** after hearing about the danger.\n10. The company kept a **watchful** eye on costs.\n11. A **circumspect** leader considers risks before acting.\n12. Her **circumspect** response avoided unnecessary conflict.\n13. The lawyer gave a **guarded** answer.\n14. The witness sounded **guarded**, as if hiding something.\n15. A **careful** analyst checks evidence before making claims.\n\n---\n\n# Compact Daily Summary Table — Day 1 Part 2\n\n| No. | Word         | Core Meaning               | Bangla            | GRE Synonyms                       | Antonym       |\n| --: | ------------ | -------------------------- | ----------------- | ---------------------------------- | ------------- |\n|  16 | Homogeneous  | same kind throughout       | সমজাতীয়           | uniform, consistent, unvarying     | heterogeneous |\n|  17 | Humdrum      | boring and routine         | একঘেয়ে            | monotonous, dull, tedious          | exciting      |\n|  18 | Insipid      | tasteless or dull          | স্বাদহীন, নীরস    | bland, vapid, flavorless           | flavorful     |\n|  19 | Loquacious   | very talkative             | বাচাল             | garrulous, voluble, verbose        | taciturn      |\n|  20 | Misanthropic | disliking people           | মানুষবিদ্বেষী     | cynical, reclusive, antisocial     | philanthropic |\n|  21 | Misnomer     | wrong name                 | ভুল নাম           | misnaming, inaccurate label        | correct label |\n|  22 | Negligent    | careless in duty           | অবহেলাকারী        | careless, remiss, lax              | diligent      |\n|  23 | Obsequious   | excessively flattering     | চাটুকার           | servile, fawning, sycophantic      | independent   |\n|  24 | Placate      | calm anger                 | শান্ত করা         | appease, pacify, mollify           | provoke       |\n|  25 | Proclivity   | natural tendency           | প্রবণতা           | inclination, propensity, penchant  | aversion      |\n|  26 | Puerile      | childish, immature         | শিশুসুলভ          | juvenile, immature, infantile      | mature        |\n|  27 | Quixotic     | idealistic but unrealistic | অবাস্তব আদর্শবাদী | idealistic, impractical, visionary | practical     |\n|  28 | Spendthrift  | reckless spender           | অমিতব্যয়ী         | profligate, extravagant, prodigal  | frugal        |\n|  29 | Taciturn     | habitually quiet           | স্বল্পভাষী        | reserved, reticent, laconic        | loquacious    |\n|  30 | Wary         | cautious of danger         | সতর্ক             | cautious, vigilant, circumspect    | reckless      |\n\n---\n\n# Revision Section\n\nFor Day 1 Part 2, revise in this order:\n\n**Round 1 — Fast meaning:**\nHomogeneous = same; Humdrum = boring; Insipid = dull/tasteless; Loquacious = talkative; Misanthropic = people-hating; Misnomer = wrong name.\n\n**Round 2 — Confusing pairs:**\nLoquacious ≠ Taciturn\nWary ≠ Weary\nSpendthrift ≠ Thrifty\nMisanthropic ≠ Philanthropic\nHomogeneous ≠ Heterogeneous\nObsequious ≠ Obedient\nPuerile ≠ Pure\nQuixotic ≠ Exotic\n\n**Round 3 — High-priority GRE words:**\nFocus extra on **obsequious, placate, proclivity, puerile, quixotic, spendthrift, taciturn, wary**.\n\n---",
